        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">Boeing's Big Capital Raise Rewards Banks</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-nov-4-2.jpg" alt="Boeing's Big Capital Raise Rewards Banks" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Boeing <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/2024/11/01/boeing-bankers-grab-up-to-300-million-in-capital-raise-fees/" target="_blank">raised</a> over $23 billion, paying hefty fees to lead banks like Goldman Sachs, each pocketing up to $75 million. This cash influx comes ahead of the US election as equity markets cool. The funds aim to strengthen Boeing’s balance sheet and fend off a credit rating downgrade. Despite a strong IPO market since 2021, firms are cautious. Boeing’s capital raise included a significant common share sale and convertible preferred stock. With market uncertainties looming, this move underscores the lengths companies are willing to go to secure financial stability.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
