        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">Wirecard Critics Close Hedge Fund</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Neil Campling and Toby Clothier, known for spotting Wirecard's fraud early, have <a href="https://www.hedgeweek.com/size-constraints-prompt-wirecard-critics-to-close-hedge-fund/" target="_blank">shut down</a> their hedge fund, Chameleon Global Master Fund, citing its small scale. Launched under Ronit Capital, the fund's $2.7 million size was unsustainable. Despite their keen eye for market scrutiny, they expressed doubt about AI’s long-term economic hype, comparing it to the dot-com bubble. Campling will now join Bloomberg as an M&A correspondent while Clothier explores new ventures.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
