        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">LA Votes on Record School Bond Measure</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Los Angeles voters are set to decide on a <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/11/01/la-voters-to-decide-on-record-9-billion-of-bonds-for-schools/" target="_blank">$9 billion</a> school bond proposal, the largest in the district’s history. Funds would modernize outdated school facilities, add air conditioning, improve Wi-Fi, and enhance accessibility. With enrollment declining and budget strains, proponents argue that revitalizing schools is essential to attract families back. If approved, property taxes could rise by about $25 per $100,000 of home value.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
