        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">Ares Expands Assets Amid Lending Surge</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Ares Management grew its assets to <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/company-news/2024/11/01/ares-grows-cash-pool-as-demand-for-private-lending-soars/" target="_blank">$464 billion</a> in Q3, up 17% from last year, fueled by interest in private lending and strategic acquisitions. Their revenue rose 68% to $1.1 billion, with $20.9 billion in fresh capital raised. CEO Michael Arougheti noted the rise of private debt, pointing to reduced reliance on traditional banks. Ares remains focused on diverse investments, including real estate and infrastructure.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
